The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, November 24, 2003 				 Film fest on human rights
 A STAFF REPORTER																								The US consulate-general will present the first Human Rights Watch International Film Festival at the American Center from Monday. During the two-day festival, being held in collaboration with the International Foundation for Crime Prevention and Victim Care, Chennai, discussions on cinema-related topics have also been organised.																								On Monday, Prof Sanjoy Mukherjee, head of the department of film studies, Jadavpur University, will speak on Film as a Medium of Social Change. An award-winning Palestinian romantic film, Ranas Wedding, will be screened.																								Film-maker Anindita Sarbadhicary will talk about Film-maker as an Activist/Activist as a Film-maker on Tuesday afternoon. Two documentary films, focussing on socio-political situations, Pinochets Children from Germany and War Takes, a Colombia-England joint production, will be shown.
